WEBVTT

00:06.931 --> 00:09.000
[breathing heavily]

00:14.103 --> 00:17.000
[eerie atmospheric music]

00:42.517 --> 00:45.793
[screams echo]

01:05.793 --> 01:08.000
- What happened to you?

01:11.310 --> 01:12.413
Ahhhh!

01:24.758 --> 01:26.896
- They're in here.

01:26.965 --> 01:28.344
- You seen 'em?

01:28.413 --> 01:30.103
- Smell 'em.

01:30.172 --> 01:32.517
- We'll get these horses
gored in that thick shit.

01:32.586 --> 01:36.896
- Well I'm not leaving $100,000
worth of bulls in that thicket.

01:36.965 --> 01:38.827
- Send in the dogs.

01:38.896 --> 01:40.068
- [whistles]

01:42.448 --> 01:44.068
- Hey Travis, why don't
you come on over, bring a horse,

01:44.137 --> 01:46.379
We'll go for a ride,
maybe chase some cows.

01:46.448 --> 01:48.551
- You've horse traded
me enough, Travis.

01:48.620 --> 01:50.206
Time I horse traded you.

01:50.275 --> 01:51.275
- [chuckles]

01:51.344 --> 01:53.172
- Oh, you think that's funny?

01:53.241 --> 01:55.068
[bulls grunt]

01:55.137 --> 01:58.034
- Boy, if this don't
pucker your red eye,

01:58.103 --> 01:59.862
I guess nothing will, huh?
- Here we go.

01:59.931 --> 02:01.586
- All right.
Nobody be a hero.

02:01.655 --> 02:02.689
Turn together.

02:02.758 --> 02:04.724
- Let's go.

02:13.137 --> 02:14.517
- All right,
let's split up.

02:14.586 --> 02:15.724
- Yah!

02:17.413 --> 02:19.689
- Hey hey!
- Take that angle!

02:23.241 --> 02:24.689
- Ho ho!

02:24.758 --> 02:25.965
[men shouting]
[bulls grunting]

02:26.034 --> 02:27.551
Shit! They're moving this way.
Watch out!

02:27.620 --> 02:29.034
Everybody stay back!

02:30.482 --> 02:32.068
- I'm coming around!

02:32.137 --> 02:33.137
- Goddamn they're angry.

02:33.206 --> 02:35.551
- Get the fuck out of here!

02:35.620 --> 02:37.724
- Push 'em out this way.
Hurry up!

02:38.793 --> 02:40.068
- Here they come!

02:42.931 --> 02:44.172
- Go go go go!

02:49.931 --> 02:51.931
[dogs barking]

02:52.000 --> 02:53.793
[dog whimpers]

02:55.034 --> 02:56.931
[leaves rustling, bulls moo]

03:03.310 --> 03:05.275
- Kayce!

03:07.965 --> 03:09.551
- Yah! Get out of there.

03:32.344 --> 03:35.344
- Goddamn boss,
that was awful reckless.

03:35.413 --> 03:37.758
- It's only reckless if you
can't see it through.

03:41.551 --> 03:43.413
Hell of a morning, huh?

03:50.931 --> 03:54.068
[theme music]

05:03.000 --> 05:05.000
[soft music plays]

05:36.034 --> 05:38.620
["What Comes Naturally"
by Blackberry Smoke plays]

05:46.620 --> 05:48.482
- Get yourself, Kayce, go on.

05:55.241 --> 05:58.344
♪ Hey pretty baby come and spend
a little time with me ♪

06:00.965 --> 06:04.310
♪ Hey pretty baby come and spend
a little time with me ♪

06:07.379 --> 06:10.275
♪ Hey pretty baby come
and spend a little time ♪

06:10.344 --> 06:12.965
♪ I ain't got
but one thing in mind... ♪

06:15.896 --> 06:17.206
- What's the count?

06:17.275 --> 06:19.965
- 800 so far.

06:20.034 --> 06:22.413
Probably another
200 in the mix.

06:24.620 --> 06:25.931
- Shit.

06:26.000 --> 06:27.689
- Hey! Keep those bulls
away from the cows!

06:27.758 --> 06:29.068
- Move, move!

06:29.137 --> 06:30.275
Hey bulls!

06:35.655 --> 06:36.827
- Jimmy, get up here!

06:36.896 --> 06:38.379
Get ready to close
that fucking gate.

06:40.448 --> 06:41.931
- Get in there, Jimmy.

06:42.000 --> 06:43.000
- Get in there.
Go get that gate.

06:44.517 --> 06:47.000
- They're fucking angry!
- No shit they're angry.

06:47.068 --> 06:48.310
Their job is to fuck, Jimmy.

06:48.379 --> 06:50.448
And they ain't fucked
in six months.

06:50.517 --> 06:51.689
Better grow eyes in the
back of your head

06:51.758 --> 06:53.068
with these bastards.

06:56.758 --> 06:59.620
- These go over by
the squeeze shoot.

06:59.689 --> 07:03.275
And this is the Lane Pulsator IV

07:03.344 --> 07:06.103
Electronic Bull Ejaculator
for Artificial Insemination.

07:06.172 --> 07:07.241
- What are you gonna do with it?

07:07.310 --> 07:08.827
- I'm not doing
anything with it.

07:08.896 --> 07:10.965
One of you are.

07:11.034 --> 07:13.034
- Yeah. That's a low-man's work.

07:13.103 --> 07:15.172
- Who's low-man?

07:15.241 --> 07:16.448
Bullshit.

07:16.517 --> 07:18.275
- Yeah, you'll be covered
in that, too.

07:18.344 --> 07:20.655
- I ain't no fucking wrangler.
I'm the groomer.

07:20.724 --> 07:22.034
Make Gilligan do it.

07:22.103 --> 07:24.137
- Oh, I plan to.
But you're doing it with him.

07:26.551 --> 07:28.068
- Excuse me.

07:28.137 --> 07:29.551
Who runs this outfit?

07:44.448 --> 07:46.931
Looking for some day-work,
if you have any.

07:47.000 --> 07:49.586
Trying to make my way
to Arizona.

07:49.655 --> 07:52.413
References available
upon request.

07:58.206 --> 08:01.344
- Well you can make your case
to that fella right over there.

08:15.655 --> 08:17.379
- Howdy.
- Hi.

08:17.448 --> 08:19.206
- They call me Cowboy.

08:19.275 --> 08:22.689
Gentleman tells me you might
have some day work for me.

08:22.758 --> 08:26.310
Nice spread you got here...

08:26.379 --> 08:30.620
[soft music plays]

08:54.448 --> 08:57.172
- You have a fundraiser
dinner tonight.

08:57.241 --> 08:59.310
Another one tomorrow in Helena,

08:59.379 --> 09:03.206
then Thursday at the Stock Farm
in Hamilton.

09:03.275 --> 09:04.793
My parents are gonna be
in Missoula this weekend.

09:04.862 --> 09:07.862
They'd love to meet you.

09:07.931 --> 09:10.275
No pressure.

09:16.620 --> 09:18.137
- I'm gonna grab some coffee.
You want some?

09:18.206 --> 09:19.827
- What?

09:19.896 --> 09:21.448
- Coffee.

09:21.517 --> 09:22.758
- Oh, I'm out.
Do you wanna grab us some?

09:22.827 --> 09:25.862
- Great idea.

09:35.758 --> 09:36.965
- Could I have
two coffees please.

09:37.034 --> 09:40.000
- Mm-hm. Choose a selection
from the board.

09:43.379 --> 09:45.551
- You know what.
You choose one.

09:55.965 --> 09:57.620
You know they have
machines for this.

09:57.689 --> 09:59.379
- Yeah, but this is like,
a way fresher brew.

09:59.448 --> 10:00.689
Better than a regular drip.

10:04.482 --> 10:06.896
- Well I see why
the long line.

10:06.965 --> 10:08.241
- Oh yeah, people wait
all day for this stuff.

10:12.482 --> 10:14.137
- Hey, I would let
that rest for like...

10:29.344 --> 10:30.310
- Hey.

10:30.379 --> 10:32.172
- Thank God. Caffeine.

10:32.241 --> 10:35.310
A 'pour-over,'
God bless you.

10:35.379 --> 10:38.000
The best measure of progress
in a town is decent coffee.

10:51.310 --> 10:53.068
- And obviously,

10:53.137 --> 10:55.068
there's a rent reduction
for a multiyear lease.

10:55.137 --> 10:57.551
- If I'm in Bozeman
this time next year,

10:57.620 --> 11:00.620
Jason here has
instructions to poison me.

11:00.689 --> 11:03.310
Let's start with six months.

11:03.379 --> 11:05.448
- Six-month leases
do require payment in advance.

11:05.517 --> 11:06.793
- That's fine.

11:06.862 --> 11:07.931
Get me account information

11:08.000 --> 11:09.482
and I'll have the money
wired tomorrow.

11:09.551 --> 11:11.034
Furnish it.

11:11.103 --> 11:12.931
- Schwartz and Meyer in Bozeman.

11:13.000 --> 11:14.931
I guess we're a real city now.

11:15.000 --> 11:16.793
And I didn't think Bozeman
could grow any more

11:16.862 --> 11:19.344
after the co-op moved in.
- What's the Co-op?

11:19.413 --> 11:21.000
- It's kinda like a Whole Foods.

11:21.068 --> 11:23.517
- There's a Whole Foods here??

11:23.586 --> 11:25.655
Thank you

11:31.482 --> 11:32.586
- How's the space?

11:32.655 --> 11:35.517
- It'll do.
I found one.

11:35.586 --> 11:36.793
- Yeah? Who?

11:36.862 --> 11:38.758
- State Prosecutor
in Custer County.

11:38.827 --> 11:41.586
She clerked for Stewart in 2014.

11:41.655 --> 11:45.655
Former rodeo queen.
Pretty girl.

11:45.724 --> 11:47.517
- Pretty doesn't matter.

11:47.586 --> 11:49.103
- Yeah, it does.

11:53.793 --> 11:57.551
- Jesus, she...
She looks like you.

11:57.620 --> 12:01.137
- Jamie's gonna
fucking hate her.

12:01.206 --> 12:03.689
- Yeah.

12:22.965 --> 12:24.724
- Here's my issue, Chairman.

12:24.793 --> 12:27.655
I've got plenty,
but my first one,

12:27.724 --> 12:29.724
is we already have a casino.

12:29.793 --> 12:32.379
It would seem to me improving it
makes much more sense

12:32.448 --> 12:35.000
than building one 90 miles
off the reservation.

12:35.068 --> 12:39.034
- Our reservation
is not a destination--

12:39.103 --> 12:43.034
it's a gas stop on the way
to destinations.

12:43.103 --> 12:45.448
Truckers and buses filled
with senior citizens

12:45.517 --> 12:47.068
putting nickels
in slot machines

12:47.137 --> 12:48.241
will not improve our schools--

12:48.310 --> 12:49.724
- So you want to spend
$200 million

12:49.793 --> 12:51.344
building another one??

12:51.413 --> 12:53.758
Off-site casinos come
with regulations,

12:53.827 --> 12:55.551
they come with partners
we don't control--

12:55.620 --> 12:58.103
- It won't be off-site.

12:58.172 --> 13:01.000
We will own the land.

13:01.068 --> 13:04.862
And once we do, we annex it
into the reservation.

13:04.931 --> 13:06.068
- Can we do that?

13:06.137 --> 13:07.827
- The precedent's already set.

13:07.896 --> 13:12.275
The Chumash did it
in Santa Ynez.

13:12.344 --> 13:15.931
We can build businesses--
hotels, restaurant.

13:16.000 --> 13:17.931
With no state oversight.

13:18.000 --> 13:20.827
Because it's part
of the reservation.

13:20.896 --> 13:23.793
All I need is council approval
for the loan.

13:27.827 --> 13:29.344
- Ambitious.

13:29.413 --> 13:31.965
- It's what I was elected to be.

13:32.034 --> 13:34.793
- You were elected to bring
change to the reservation.

13:34.862 --> 13:37.517
This isn't change.
This is the same thing

13:37.586 --> 13:39.379
white man's been doing
to us for centuries.

13:39.448 --> 13:40.413
And now you're doing it.

13:40.482 --> 13:42.896
- Yes. At last.

13:42.965 --> 13:45.000
Someone is doing it to them.

13:45.068 --> 13:47.517
This is where change begins.

13:50.965 --> 13:53.000
- I don't see anything
in this proposal

13:53.068 --> 13:54.758
that shows how the money
from this development

13:54.827 --> 13:57.103
is gonna help the community.

13:57.172 --> 13:59.137
Just your promise it will.

13:59.206 --> 14:01.068
And promises are how
we got on the reservation

14:01.137 --> 14:03.758
in the first place.

14:03.827 --> 14:07.103
- Trusting them is what
put us on reservations.

14:07.172 --> 14:10.758
And I don't trust them.

14:10.827 --> 14:13.310
- You don't get my vote.

14:16.034 --> 14:17.655
- Do I need it?

14:25.448 --> 14:26.758
I don't need it.

14:28.551 --> 14:30.068
- Well you will, Tom.

15:00.000 --> 15:02.137
- Well, it's good to see you.

15:02.206 --> 15:04.655
So how can I help?

15:04.724 --> 15:07.172
- I've reconsidered.

15:07.241 --> 15:09.206
The job you offered.
I've reconsidered.

15:09.275 --> 15:11.103
- Uh...

15:11.172 --> 15:14.103
The money we earmarked for that
Native American Studies program

15:14.172 --> 15:16.620
was re-allocated
until next semester

15:16.689 --> 15:18.413
when we can find a professor.

15:18.482 --> 15:20.068
I thought you didn't want
to leave the school

15:20.137 --> 15:22.551
on the reservation
with one less teacher.

15:22.620 --> 15:25.862
You were pretty firm on that,
if I recall.

15:25.931 --> 15:27.517
- I'm not leaving.

15:27.586 --> 15:28.965
What I mean is: I want both.

15:29.034 --> 15:30.655
I can teach mornings
at the high school,

15:30.724 --> 15:33.034
and afternoons or evenings
here at the university.

15:33.103 --> 15:36.862
- That's a full plate,
and a long drive.

15:36.931 --> 15:38.206
- I'm aware of that.

15:40.551 --> 15:43.137
- I have a class--
American History.

15:43.206 --> 15:44.896
It needs a professor.

15:44.965 --> 15:47.827
That gets you in the door
until we can get your classes

15:47.896 --> 15:49.241
on the fall schedule.

15:49.310 --> 15:51.827
- What era of American History.

15:51.896 --> 15:55.275
- Columbus's arrival to the
Declaration of Independence.

15:55.344 --> 15:57.482
- Columbus.

15:57.551 --> 15:59.206
- Are you comfortable with that?
- Depends.

15:59.275 --> 16:02.172
Which version of Columbus's
history am I teaching?

16:02.241 --> 16:04.344
- Yours, Mrs. Dutton.

16:04.413 --> 16:09.103
- Long.
My last name is Long.

16:09.172 --> 16:10.862
It used to be "Long Spear,"

16:10.931 --> 16:13.344
until my grandfather
was taken from his parents

16:13.413 --> 16:14.758
and sent to a Catholic school

16:14.827 --> 16:16.689
funded by the Bureau
of Indian Affairs,

16:16.758 --> 16:18.068
where they changed his name

16:18.137 --> 16:20.482
and tried to teach him
how not to be Indian.

16:23.689 --> 16:25.586
I look forward to teaching young
minds all about the man

16:25.655 --> 16:27.896
who introduced genocide
to the Western Hemisphere.

16:50.172 --> 16:53.241
- My God.

16:53.310 --> 16:54.620
You Beth?

16:54.689 --> 16:56.000
- You Cassidy?

16:56.068 --> 16:57.413
- Whew.

16:57.482 --> 16:59.310
My part of Montana you can
stand on a can of tuna

16:59.379 --> 17:01.275
and see the entire state
from there.

17:01.344 --> 17:03.862
- Not here.

17:03.931 --> 17:05.413
- I'm very curious to learn
what I can do for you.

17:05.482 --> 17:09.068
- Oh I think it's
what we can do for you.

17:09.137 --> 17:11.000
Come inside.

17:15.275 --> 17:16.931
Here.

17:20.586 --> 17:24.723
- We're looking
at three candidates to support.

17:24.792 --> 17:28.000
And wanted to gauge your
interest.

17:29.655 --> 17:34.103
- I'm flattered by the offer.

17:34.172 --> 17:36.448
I have to ask: why aren't you
supporting your son?

17:36.517 --> 17:39.000
- Clearly you haven't met him.

17:39.068 --> 17:40.172
- We want what's best
for Montana.

17:40.241 --> 17:41.896
And right now, that...

17:41.965 --> 17:43.620
that feels like you.

17:45.275 --> 17:46.758
- Can you walk my father through

17:46.827 --> 17:48.482
the wounded veterans
charity you started.

17:48.551 --> 17:51.655
- We save horses from
slaughterhouses in Canada

17:51.724 --> 17:53.448
and use them for equine therapy

17:53.517 --> 17:56.965
with war veterans
suffering from PTSD.

17:58.103 --> 18:00.793
- Well then...

18:00.862 --> 18:04.137
Be hard for either side
to argue against.

18:04.206 --> 18:07.965
- I'm late.
I gotta go, Daddy. Love you.

18:08.034 --> 18:10.310
- Don't change the hair.

18:13.379 --> 18:16.068
- I'm a little worried I won't
get the voter turnout.

18:16.137 --> 18:18.931
I'm from eastern Montana,
towns with 600 people,

18:19.000 --> 18:20.551
not a lot of voters there.

18:20.620 --> 18:22.344
- You let me worry about votes.

18:22.413 --> 18:25.068
You just worry about being you.

18:26.448 --> 18:28.206
- Okay.

18:33.482 --> 18:36.275
[playing guitar]

19:08.068 --> 19:10.448
- What's your name?

19:10.517 --> 19:12.689
- Cowboy.

19:12.758 --> 19:15.206
- Your name's Cowboy.

19:15.275 --> 19:16.827
Shit. We're all cowboys.

19:16.896 --> 19:19.275
- Ha. The hell you are.

19:21.896 --> 19:23.586
And you...

19:23.655 --> 19:25.275
you ride a horse
like a teenager fucks--

19:25.344 --> 19:27.275
bouncing up and down
with your eyes wide,

19:27.344 --> 19:29.344
stunned you're doing it at all.

19:29.413 --> 19:33.275
- Only cowboy thing I seen you
do is clean your plate.

19:33.344 --> 19:35.068
Stand up and tell me
I can't cowboy.

19:35.137 --> 19:36.586
- I didn't say you can't.

19:36.655 --> 19:38.517
I said he can't.

19:38.586 --> 19:41.689
And he sure as hell can't.

19:41.758 --> 19:43.931
And you don't want
me standing up, boy.

19:44.000 --> 19:45.689
I'll beat you
like a rented mule.

19:50.482 --> 19:55.241
- There's one rule
on this ranch, Cowboy.

19:55.310 --> 19:57.448
If you wanna fight somebody,

19:57.517 --> 19:58.931
you fight me.

19:59.000 --> 20:00.896
I guess you forgot that rule,
right?

20:00.965 --> 20:02.448
Go sit down.

20:06.275 --> 20:08.758
[singing and playing guitar
in distance]

20:21.896 --> 20:23.137
Lloyd,

20:23.206 --> 20:25.068
Go tell Elvis supper's ready.

20:25.137 --> 20:26.275
- I'll tell him for you.

20:35.655 --> 20:37.896
♪ ...something you'll
never know ♪

20:41.241 --> 20:45.206
♪ Your only home ♪

20:48.965 --> 20:52.620
- I see your voice
didn't get any happier.

20:52.689 --> 20:56.172
- Well I guess neither did I.

20:56.241 --> 20:58.310
Hell I ain't seen you since--
- The Haythorne.

20:58.379 --> 21:00.482
Nebraska.

21:00.551 --> 21:02.931
Heard you did a stint.

21:03.000 --> 21:06.827
- Seven years.

21:06.896 --> 21:09.827
- Yeah well,
it's behind you now.

21:09.896 --> 21:14.172
Keep it there, son.

21:14.241 --> 21:15.655
- I'm trying.

21:17.620 --> 21:19.896
How'd this place find you?

21:19.965 --> 21:21.620
- I found it.

21:21.689 --> 21:24.034
- This ranch...

21:24.103 --> 21:26.931
it's ain't like no place
you ever worked.

21:27.000 --> 21:28.931
You might wanna think
about making a U-turn.

21:30.793 --> 21:32.413
- Work's the same.

21:32.482 --> 21:34.344
Just the ranch name
that changes.

21:34.413 --> 21:36.793
- No. This one's different.

21:36.862 --> 21:40.000
Reminds me of that place
down on the border.

21:40.068 --> 21:43.448
Fuckin' drug-runners, militia,
and all that shit.

21:45.068 --> 21:48.862
- There ain't
no border here, son.

21:48.931 --> 21:51.586
- Oh yes there is.

21:51.655 --> 21:53.758
We just can't see it.

21:58.517 --> 22:01.034
- Don't seem like you've made
a friend in the foreman.

22:01.103 --> 22:03.655
- Keep an eye on him.

22:03.724 --> 22:05.310
Keep an eye on all of 'em.

22:06.896 --> 22:10.172
How long gonna stay?

22:10.241 --> 22:12.241
- Maybe I'll just push 'em
out to pasture

22:12.310 --> 22:14.896
and then head south.

22:14.965 --> 22:17.862
- That's a good idea.

22:17.931 --> 22:20.275
When you leave I'm
going with you.

22:20.344 --> 22:23.068
- You don't need permission
to leave, Walker.

22:23.137 --> 22:25.000
- Here you do.

22:41.724 --> 22:44.482
[guitar plays]

22:59.275 --> 23:00.896
- How you doin'?

23:00.965 --> 23:04.103
- How are you doing?

23:04.172 --> 23:06.620
- I'm...

23:06.689 --> 23:09.000
Doing, you know?

23:09.068 --> 23:12.793
- Yeah.

23:12.862 --> 23:14.896
- Can you give us a minute?

23:14.965 --> 23:17.379
- Good to see you Kayce.

23:17.448 --> 23:19.344
- You too.

23:28.448 --> 23:31.586
I was hoping I made it
before he fell asleep.

23:31.655 --> 23:33.034
- You didn't.

23:36.586 --> 23:39.758
- Tell me how this works,
Monica.

23:39.827 --> 23:42.034
I'm his father.
You can't keep me from him.

23:44.000 --> 23:45.413
- I'm not trying to
keep you from him,

23:45.482 --> 23:50.241
I just have to shield him
from what you've done.

23:50.310 --> 23:52.758
I can't let him see it
catch up to you.

23:55.379 --> 23:56.862
